body:
@tj-gayman

dear sky,

you are wonderful! the past few weeks have been awsome talking to you, and i just couldn’t wait for you to find out who i am. so here we are! i’m alyssa, and i drew this for you! for context, this is a tyrus and muffy carnival double date. tj won a game of ring toss, and he asked cyrus which prize he wanted. cyrus spotted a weird little pig with a chef hat and knew that was the prize he wanted! on the other hand, marty and buffy have been competing and play-fighting all day. after buffy lost to marty at balloon darts, she had to buy him ice cream. he caught her off guard and got some ice cream on her nose! anyway, i hope you like this, i’m so happy with how it came out! i didn’t draw the background, its a blurred stock photo lol. i also added the time lapse in case you were interested in that! i don’t want this to get too long, but feel free to message me whenever!

love, vcg💖

summary: @blueberry-my-hero-macadamia  I'm also your last minute valentine because I stole you from Amanda bc I saw tarty and got excited...
body:
@blueberry-my-hero-macadamia

I’m also your last minute valentine because I stole you from Amanda bc I saw tarty and got excited but ended up writing tyrus


TJ flinched as a piece of popcorn hit him on the nose. “Oh, is this what we’re doing now?”

Cyrus crossed his arms in front of him and avoided eye contact. “I have no clue what you’re talking about,” he bit his lip to hide his smile.

He took small handful of popcorn out of the bucket and chucked it at Cyrus.

“First strike,” Cyrus stood up and pointed at him. “You took the first strike, I want that on record.”

“Oh, did I?” TJ plucked a piece that fell onto the table. “What about the one that hit my nose,” he threw it and it bounced off of his shirt.

“What a baseless accusation,” Cyrus took a step towards him and tossed a piece into TJ’s hair.

“You’re such a dork,” TJ pulled him closer by his shirt until their noses were touching.

“Maybe so,” Cyrus whispered and pressed his lips against his.

TJ tangled his hand in his hair and pulled away to kiss him on the cheek before bringing their lips together again.

“And that’s enough of that,” he jumped at hearing his sister’s voice.

“Amber,” he groaned and sunk back into the couch. “You always do this.”

“Hi,” she ignored him and held her hand out to Cyrus. “I’m Amber.”

“Hi,” Cyrus stuck his hand out and smiled. “I’m Cyrus, TJ’s boyfriend.” He leaned in to TJ’s side. “Right?” He whispered.

“Of course,” he took his hand.

“I just wanted to have a little talk with you,” she crossed one leg over the other and rested her hands on her knee. “One on one,” she glanced at him.

“You’re not intimidating,” he shook his head. “And I’m not letting you scare off another one.”

“You just contradicted yourself,” she smiled smugly.

“You’re so annoying,” he put his head on Cyrus’ shoulder and closed his eyes. “Get it over with, do your thing.”

“Okay,” she said sweetly and turned to face Cyrus. “If you dare,” she lowered her voice and tilted her face forward. “Hurt my brother.”

TJ felt Cyrus’ hand tighten around his. “I wasn’t planning on it,” he whispered.

“Good,” she narrowed her eyes. “Because if you were.”

He looked around the room for a minute. “What happens if I do?”

“Oh, so you are?” She tilted her head and leaned forward.

“No!” He shook his head. “That’s not what I mean at all.”

“So what are your intentions, then?”

“Oh my god,” TJ spoke up. “You’re already cutting into our date. Do you have to be so dramatic about it?”

She shushed him. “Answer the question, Cyrus.”

“I intend to…” He thought for a moment. “What does that question even mean, honestly?”

“I don’t know,” she whispered. “I just hear it in movies a lot.”

“Movie logic makes no sense,” he laughed. “You ever notice that when a burglary takes place the thieves always tilt the pictures sideways?”

“What do you mean movie logic? I always tilt the pictures sideways when I rob people it adds to the drama of it all.”

“We should rob a house together sometime.” They both looked at each other and laughed.

“Okay,” TJ stood up. “Well, this is all well and good now so you should go,” he offered her hand to help her up.

“I think I want to keep hanging out with my new best friend,” she made no effort to move.

“I think I want to hang out with him more,” he spoke through clenched teeth.

“Alright,” she shrugged. “I see where I’m not wanted.” She slowly headed upstairs and disappeared around the doorway.

“So,” TJ turned towards him. “What do you want to do?”

Cyrus shook his head and shrugged.

“You want to keep hanging out with her don’t you?” TJ rolled his eyes and laughed. “Amber?” He called.

“One step ahead of you,” she walked in carrying a collection of movies.

“You’re not intimidating,” he shook his head. “And I’m not letting you scare off another one.”

“You just contradicted yourself,” she smiled smugly.

“You’re so annoying,” he put his head on Cyrus’ shoulder and closed his eyes. “Get it over with, do your thing.”

“Okay,” she said sweetly and turned to face Cyrus. “If you dare,” she lowered her voice and tilted her face forward. “Hurt my brother.”

TJ felt Cyrus’ hand tighten around his. “I wasn’t planning on it,” he whispered.

“Good,” she narrowed her eyes. “Because if you were.”

He looked around the room for a minute. “What happens if I do?”

“Oh, so you are?” She tilted her head and leaned forward.

“No!” He shook his head. “That’s not what I mean at all.”

“So what are your intentions, then?”

“Oh my god,” TJ spoke up. “You’re already cutting into our date. Do you have to be so dramatic about it?”

She shushed him. “Answer the question, Cyrus.”

“I intend to…” He thought for a moment. “What does that question even mean, honestly?”

“I don’t know,” she whispered. “I just hear it in movies a lot.”

“Movie logic makes no sense,” he laughed. “You ever notice that when a burglary takes place the thieves always tilt the pictures sideways?”

“What do you mean movie logic? I always tilt the pictures sideways when I rob people it adds to the drama of it all.”

“We should rob a house together sometime.” They both looked at each other and laughed.

“Okay,” TJ stood up. “Well, this is all well and good now so you should go,” he offered her hand to help her up.

“I think I want to keep hanging out with my new best friend,” she made no effort to move.

“I think I want to hang out with him more,” he spoke through clenched teeth.

“Alright,” she shrugged. “I see where I’m not wanted.” She slowly headed upstairs and disappeared around the doorway.

“So,” TJ turned towards him. “What do you want to do?”

Cyrus shook his head and shrugged.

“You want to keep hanging out with her don’t you?” TJ rolled his eyes and laughed. “Amber?” He called.

“One step ahead of you,” she walked in carrying a collection of movies.
